OL,3,CElectric charging points could become
OL,4,Cmandatory for all new homes in Wales
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government says the move
OL,7,Fwill save people money over time,
OL,8,Fcosting an additional #1,000 on the
OL,9,Fprice of a new home. If fitted at a
OL,10,Flater date, retrofitting a charge
OL,11,Fpoint could cost on average #2,300.
OL,13,FA Welsh Government spokesperson said:
OL,14,F"With an increase of electric vehicles
OL,15,Fexpected on our roads in the coming
OL,16,Fyears it's important we have the
OL,17,Finfrastructure in place to support
OL,18,Fthese vehicles, especially in people's
OL,19,Fhomes where, today, most charging
OL,20,Ftakes place.
